1
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:08,280
AN ADAPTATION OF THE NOVEL BY HUDANAJWA

2
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:17,240
<i>Darling, I can't lose you.</i>

3
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>I love you so much.</i>

4
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:30,160
What's with you? Are you having a fit?

5
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:34,480
Good morning, ma'am.
Are you here to help me cook?

6
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,319
Am I your maid?

7
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:39,399
- A maid, huh?
- What's your problem?

8
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:42,239
Be mature, Aina.
Enough with your tantrums.

9
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,519
You're not a child.

10
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,520
Tantrum?

11
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,599
Hey.

12
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:47,800
It's because of you.

13
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:51,759
If you hadn't come here,
I would've married Ridz.

14
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,840
This house wouldn't be in shambles.

15
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,959
Just wait.

16
00:00:55,960 --> 00:01:00,919
Mom will soon see your true colors

17
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:03,720
and get you out of this house.

18
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:05,800
Get me out?

19
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:07,799
Okay.

20
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,200
We'll see.

21
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:14,840
I'll be here with Ridz.

22
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:18,160
Then what?

23
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,040
Ridz will marry me.

24
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:25,599
Then I will tell him to divorce you.

25
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:26,800
Divorce?

26
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:28,760
And then?

27
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:32,319
And then?

28
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,439
What else?

29
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:36,080
You go live elsewhere. What else?

30
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,560
Oh, Aina.

31
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,720
And then what?

32
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:44,880
Share your fantasy with me.

33
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,480
I want to know
the extent of your delusion.

34
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:54,520
Use your brain. Don't be so thick-headed.

35
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:58,479
Think, Aina. Think.

36
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:01,639
If you drive me out of the house,
I can guarantee

37
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,480
Ridz will come with me

38
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,359
and Mom will be upset.

39
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:10,440
Even worse, you and your mom
will be thrown out of here.

40
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:12,600
Don't you dare.

41
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,759
To be evil, one must be smart.

42
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:20,680
Understand?

43
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,720
You think you're great.

44
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,560
You think you've won.

45
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:31,480
I will never leave you in peace

46
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,640
until I get what's mine.

47
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,560
And Ridz

48
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,600
is mine.

49
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,760
You are not my competition.

50
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,440
So, give up

51
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:51,120
while you can.

52
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:13,360
Datuk Zahid, the chairman
of Little Angel Kuala Lumpur,

53
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:18,600
patron of Fitrah Home,
and founder of Kasih Home.

54
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,360
That's a lot of posts.

55
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:26,119
These shelters are just fronts.

56
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:29,079
He has four main businesses in Malaysia.

57
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:32,680
Among them is an oil and gas company.

58
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:38,079
A business that imports
and exports reconditioned cars.

59
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,040
And the last one

60
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:44,040
is a gambling and casino center
all across Malaysia.

61
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,519
Damn.

62
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,080
He must be making millions.

63
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,959
Yes, Haider.

64
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:52,439
He is a multi-millionaire.

65
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:54,559
He has many properties in Paris,

66
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,840
but he's hardly ever here.

67
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:01,160
Unless he has business to attend to.

68
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:07,320
And this is his latest business venture.

69
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:10,920
A company that leases vending machines.

70
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,880
Hello, boss.

71
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,838
<i>I know you're still on leave,</i>

72
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,160
but...

73
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,078
can you come in?

74
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,439
I have something to discuss.

75
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,720
Discuss?

76
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,439
About what?

77
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:28,120
<i>About Teduh.</i>

78
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:56,040
Wow, this looks delicious.
Who made breakfast?

79
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:59,560
If not by Chef Wan,
it must be by Chef Ismail.

80
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,400
Or maybe...

81
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,760
Ratatouille made this.

82
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,919
What?

83
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,040
A rat made this?

84
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,200
I made it!

85
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:24,240
Dear, don't tell me
you're going off on an operation.

86
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,920
Yes, I have to go.

87
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,800
Okay, in that case, I'll eat all this up.

88
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,719
You don't need to eat.

89
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,080
Hang on.

90
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:37,719
Adrean can wait ten minutes.

91
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,759
Let me spend my time with my treasure.

92
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,000
Please.

93
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:46,959
Sure, he can wait ten minutes, but...

94
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,240
But what?

95
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,439
But next time,

96
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:53,440
if you have to choose
between me and the country,

97
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,840
you must choose wisely.

98
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,999
Choose your country.

99
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:02,239
Because not everyone is entrusted

100
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,600
with that responsibility.

101
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,640
If I have to

102
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,280
choose between my treasure and my country,

103
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,799
I will obviously choose my treasure.

104
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,159
- Want to know why?
- Why?

105
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:20,320
There are other people
who can take care of the country.

106
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,840
However, my treasure...

107
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:27,399
Only I can take care of her. No one else.

108
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:31,840
She's my one and only wife
in this life and the next.

109
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,119
Promise you'll finish it.

110
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:42,440
Yes, I promise.

111
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,200
Tell me.

112
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,519
Who made this?

113
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:49,840
Ratatouille or my treasure?

114
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,960
If a rat did, would you eat it?

115
00:06:55,720 --> 00:07:00,480
Take care of yourself,
your prayers, your heart.

116
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,160
I love you, treasure.

117
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,240
I love you too.

118
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,680
I'm off to work now.

119
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,120
Okay.

120
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:29,080
Hello. Peace be upon you.

121
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:33,400
He's holding a grudge against us.

122
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,559
We've carried out many operations
to take down this syndicate,

123
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,759
but it's still standing.

124
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:43,600
Now, he's meddling with Teduh.

125
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,879
We must protect the children.

126
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,720
I will not let him harm Teduh.

127
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:58,440
I don't want him to use Teduh as a front
for his illegal activities.

128
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,920
I want to know.

129
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,959
How does Zizi know Zahid?

130
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:08,279
Doesn't Radwa always volunteer there?

131
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,240
That's the problem.

132
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:12,120
Teduh...

133
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:18,239
It's the only place
where Radwa finds safety and peace.

134
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,680
Ridz, calm down.

135
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:25,320
For now, you must make sure
Radwa stays away from Teduh.

136
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:37,439
This is Radwa,
the one I always told you about.

137
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,760
She is a key person in Teduh.

138
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,359
Pleasure to meet you,

139
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,880
Miss Radwa.

140
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:51,760
Mrs. Radwa,
but you can call me Radwa, Datuk.

141
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,520
Okay.

142
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:57,720
In that case, don't call me Datuk.

143
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,520
Call me Zahid.

144
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:05,279
Radwa, Datuk and I

145
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:08,600
have a big project
and need a project manager.

146
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:15,519
We will be merging Teduh Transit Home

147
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,079
with Kasih Home.

148
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,320
Okay.

149
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:23,239
Basically, we'll name this merger
Teduh Kasih Home

150
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:26,960
and I don't see anyone else
capable of handling this place

151
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,840
other than you.

152
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,400
Okay, but what would my job scope be?

153
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,999
Basically, you'll take
good care of this place,

154
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,680
the children here, and at the same time,

155
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,360
me.

156
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,120
Just joking.

157
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:59,080
Don't worry, Radwa.

158
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:04,639
You just have to make sure the kids
get the protection they need.

159
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:07,439
You've been doing a good job so far.
Come on.

160
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,159
I have faith in you. What do you say?

161
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,000
Agree or agree?

162
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:18,200
- Agree.
- Very good.

163
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,000
By the way, do you have a business card?

164
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,160
Yes, Datuk.

165
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,880
- Okay, thank you.
- You're welcome.

166
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,520
Excuse me, Datin, Datuk.
I have to take this call.

167
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,400
Hello, Dad.

168
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,559
Dad.

169
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:58,920
Radwa. Have a seat.

170
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,160
What's the matter with Mom?

171
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:09,680
I don't know, Radwa.

172
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:14,120
Ever since you got married,

173
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:16,599
she hasn't changed.

174
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,040
She's been depressed.

175
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:22,119
She refuses to leave her room or eat.

176
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,600
She doesn't sleep at night.

177
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,440
She wouldn't even talk to me.

178
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,080
I think

179
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:35,040
your mom misses you.

180
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,280
Mom.

181
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,800
Eat some.

182
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:11,200
I've transferred money to you.

183
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,559
Also to Raudhah and Ridha.

184
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,960
You can go shopping.

185
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:24,040
Or do you want to go on a holiday?

186
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:27,600
I can book you a flight ticket.

187
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,440
Have some.

188
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,560
Mom, what's wrong?

189
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,560
Are you ill?

190
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,480
Radwa.

191
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,799
Ever since you got married,

192
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,199
I've been remembering

193
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:51,520
how I treated you.

194
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,520
I really regret it.

195
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,320
Don't say that, Mom.

196
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,360
I was cruel.

197
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,680
I berated you,

198
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,600
beat you up,

199
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:13,600
and swore at you.

200
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,640
You must've thought that

201
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,720
I don't love you.

202
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,480
No, Mom.

203
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:26,760
I don't hold it against you.

204
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:31,360
I let it slide. I have long forgiven you.

205
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:34,000
Forget about it, Mom.

206
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,600
Come, eat some.

207
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,400
Here.

208
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,280
Mom!

209
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,919
As if I have done you wrong!

210
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,759
Listen here.

211
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:04,479
I will never apologize to you
until the day I die!

212
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:07,959
Mom, I came here because I pity you.

213
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:10,199
What else is wrong?

214
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:13,199
Hey! You don't need to pity me.

215
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:15,759
I don't need your pity!

216
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:18,159
You want to know what I most regret?

217
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:23,519
I regret not beating you to death!

218
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:27,320
You know what? I hate you!

219
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,399
Mom.

220
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:34,520
I don't understand how someone like you
can escape unpunished.

221
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:39,680
You've got to marry
the man of your dreams.

222
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:42,039
You had a grand wedding.

223
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:44,799
You got everything you wanted!

224
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:49,759
You don't deserve to be happy
after taking away my wealth.

225
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:52,639
The thing I love most in this world!

226
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:56,519
You should've died!

227
00:14:56,520 --> 00:15:01,279
- Mom! Don't!
- Come here. You should've died!

228
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:04,839
- Come here.
- Mom, stop!

229
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,919
- Come!
- Mom, please!

230
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:11,120
- Get in!
- Please don't. Mom!

231
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,000
Mom.

232
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,799
Open this door.

233
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:21,280
Mom, forgive me.

234
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:23,800
Now I'm satisfied.

235
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:26,080
Stay in there.

236
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,800
Mom.

237
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,680
Hey.

238
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,160
Hey!

239
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,880
Help! Help!

240
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:52,679
<i>You know what? I hate you!</i>

241
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,399
<i>Hey!</i>

242
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:57,399
<i>You don't deserve to be happy
after taking away my wealth.</i>

243
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,799
Shut up.

244
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,400
- Shut up!
<i>- Hey!</i>

245
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:06,479
<i>- Why did you leave him?
- Where's your brother?</i>

246
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:08,560
Shut up!

247
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:14,239
- Shut up! Shut up!
<i>- You know what? I hate you!</i>

248
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,520
Shut up!

249
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:25,279
I've let it slide all this time.
I just kept quiet.

250
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:27,679
But you're getting too much!

251
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,960
Have you forgotten...

252
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,919
Have you forgotten
what your daughter did to me?

253
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:39,039
Have you forgotten
that she's your child? Our child!

254
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,719
She's all grown up.
What happened wasn't her fault.

255
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:45,039
It's fate.

256
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:48,599
Rozita, stop torturing her.

257
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,999
What if Ridz knows
what you've done to his wife?

258
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,240
What have you done to my wife?

259
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,159
Why are you here?

260
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:58,320
I called him here.

261
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,120
You called him? What for?

262
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,720
Damn you.

263
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:11,680
Darling! Open the door!

264
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,159
Darling, it's me!

265
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,520
Radwa!

266
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:21,039
- Husniya Radwa, open the door! I'm here!
<i>- You should've died!</i>

267
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,839
Husniya Radwa!

268
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:40,960
Hey, darling. What happened?

269
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,040
I'm tired.

270
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:49,840
I'm tired of all this.

271
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:54,720
It hurts. It hurts too much.

272
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:58,559
I just want to be happy.

273
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:00,640
I'm right here.

274
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:04,160
I want to feel complete.

275
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:10,400
Radwa.

276
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,160
Radwa?

277
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,200
Radwa.

278
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,440
Radwa!

279
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:22,200
Radwa, hey.

280
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:26,800
Husniya Radwa!

281
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:34,079
Did something trigger her
that caused her to faint?

282
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,200
Yes, doctor.

283
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:38,040
She may be under a lot of stress.

284
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:42,879
You must keep a patient
like your wife away from places

285
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,000
or conditions that may trigger
her emotions.

286
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,399
- How is she doing now?
- Mrs. Radwa can go home.

287
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,119
Just make sure she takes her medicine.

288
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:57,079
If her mood or behavior changes,
bring her to the hospital immediately.

289
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:58,280
- Can you do that?
- Sure.

290
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,760
Please excuse me.

291
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,040
Are you okay?

292
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,240
What happened, darling?

293
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,720
It's okay.

294
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,240
I understand.

295
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,480
Darling, listen.

296
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:44,080
When you're ready to tell me,

297
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,400
I'm here.

298
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,240
Always.

299
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:55,200
Thank you, dear.

300
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,800
The doctor told me

301
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,400
that you can go home.

302
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,600
Ready to come home?

303
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:08,480
Yes.

304
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,640
Can you smile?

305
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,360
Just a little.

306
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,960
You're cute.

307
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,560
Peace be upon you.

308
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,880
Take off your shoes.

309
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,240
Come.

310
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:45,520
Surprise. Is it nice?

311
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:49,639
Yes. Is this your house?

312
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:51,000
No.

313
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:54,320
It's our house, not just mine.

314
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:59,240
When did you buy it?
Why didn't we go to your mom's?

315
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,399
When did I buy this house?

316
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:02,560
Before we got married.

317
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:05,639
I don't want to go to my mom's.
I'm afraid you'd be stressed.

318
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:08,559
I'll always be with you here.

319
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,600
Morning, afternoon, day, and night.

320
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:14,240
Come, let's sit.

321
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,480
Come, have a seat.

322
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,600
Thank you, dear.

323
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:33,320
I appreciate all this.

324
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,600
Not yet. Here.

325
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,760
What's this for?

326
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,439
For your spending.

327
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:45,039
If you want to shop or do anything,
use this card.

328
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:47,320
Chocolate or candy, go ahead.

329
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:51,480
Thank you, dear.

330
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,120
You're welcome.

331
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:58,160
Darling,

332
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,920
I love you so much.

333
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:06,640
Can you not do that again?
I almost had a heart attack.

334
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:10,160
Sorry.

335
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,440
It's fine.

336
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:16,840
But I need you to know

337
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:20,200
that I will always be with you

338
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:23,040
forever and ever.

339
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,360
Opening up doesn't mean we're weak.

340
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:29,520
Instead, it shows your strength.

341
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:31,840
Okay?

342
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:39,480
Do you want to go eat? Fried chicken.

343
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,040
I'll pay.

344
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:42,800
Let's go.

345
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:45,680
You drive.

346
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:48,080
Yes!

347
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:55,600
- Give me the car key.
- It's in the bag.

348
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:01,880
Dear.

349
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:06,240
Do you know why
this fried chicken is so delicious?

350
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:10,840
Because...

351
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,360
it's crunchy and juicy.

352
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:17,200
Wrong. Try again.

353
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,120
We're eating it with our loved ones?

354
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:25,960
Wrong.

355
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:29,040
It's because
someone else is paying for it.

356
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:37,919
It's true. Otherwise, it's just so-so.

357
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:41,120
So-so? Yeah, sure.

358
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:45,960
Have I told you
that I met Datin Zizi recently?

359
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,400
You met Datin Zizi?

360
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,759
No, you didn't tell me.

361
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,839
Why? When?

362
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:02,159
Before I went to my mom's house.

363
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:06,480
She offered me a job
as a project manager in a new shelter.

364
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,599
Since when is there a new shelter?

365
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:12,879
It's just built.
They're naming it Teduh Kasih.

366
00:24:12,880 --> 00:24:17,079
They say no one else
can handle the project except me.

367
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,080
Wait.

368
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:21,919
"They"? Who are they?

369
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:24,480
Datin Zizi and Datuk Zahid.

370
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:31,480
Hold on.

371
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:34,960
Hello.

372
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,200
Okay, I'll be on my way.

373
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,720
Darling,

374
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:48,119
I know you're not comfortable being
at my mom's with Auntie and Aina around.

375
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:52,440
But I need to go on an operation
and I don't want you to be alone at home.

376
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:54,919
I don't mind being alone.

377
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:58,560
Please, darling. Only this time.

378
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:00,760
And one more thing.

379
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,079
Promise me not to go to Teduh alone.

380
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,399
You should go with me. Okay?

381
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:09,400
- What's wrong?
- Please, darling.

382
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,039
Promise me you won't go alone.

383
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:14,119
Okay, I promise.

384
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,960
But why? Something doesn't feel right.

385
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:21,040
Nothing. Don't worry.

386
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,120
Let's go.

387
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:30,239
For now, we haven't been able
to determine Zahid's whereabouts.

388
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:35,240
It's difficult
because he doesn't have a house here.

389
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,560
Maybe he's gone back to Paris.

390
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:41,359
- No.
- Okay.

391
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:47,479
There's no record of his private jet
leaving our airspace.

392
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:50,760
Perhaps he's left the country
by land or by sea.

393
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:52,600
Not yet.

394
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,520
He's still here.

395
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,280
- How do you know that?
- Radwa.

396
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:05,559
Two days ago,
she met with Datuk Zahid and Datin Zizi.

397
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:07,320
- What?
- I know.

398
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:12,360
I have a plan for us to locate Zahid.

399
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:28,959
Wow.

400
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,679
You can bake a cake, Radwa?

401
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:34,200
I'm impressed.

402
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:37,920
I only follow the recipe, Mom.

403
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:40,399
That's fine.

404
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,839
Even going by the recipe,
it still looks good.

405
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,479
It doesn't work for me.

406
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:46,639
Every time I bake a cake,

407
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:51,439
it doesn't rise and always goes wrong.

408
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:52,519
No idea why.

409
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,599
Just blame the oven, Mom.

410
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:57,040
How dare it ruin your cake?

411
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:01,319
Blame the oven?

412
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,040
You're funny.

413
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:05,919
Baking a cake?

414
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:09,079
Look at my daughter-in-law.

415
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:12,799
She's not only hardworking,
but she can also bake a cake.

416
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,720
I can't wait to eat it.

417
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:18,119
Well...

418
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:23,279
Baking a cake following a recipe
isn't something to brag about.

419
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:25,720
You need a recipe
for something this simple?

420
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,840
- Right?
- It's okay, Aina.

421
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:33,199
Even going by the recipe,
you can see the cake forming.

422
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:38,399
Compared to you, Aina,
who knows every recipe in the world,

423
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:42,200
but I have yet to taste
a single cake from you.

424
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,719
Maybe Aina's cake got the wrong address.

425
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:48,080
That's why it's still not here.

426
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:51,720
Could that be the case?

427
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:58,839
Sure, laugh all you want.

428
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:01,120
I curse that your cake doesn't rise.

429
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,400
Ignore her.

430
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:15,000
Hot coffee, no sugar, ready for you.

431
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:16,680
Thank you.

432
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,320
So, what's up?

433
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:23,599
I heard about your collaboration
with Datuk Zahid.

434
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:24,559
Impressive.

435
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:25,960
Thank you.

436
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:29,319
Well, let me go straight to the point.

437
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:32,760
My dad wants me to come and ask you
to arrange a meeting with Datuk Zahid.

438
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:36,079
He has many business opportunities
worth venturing into together.

439
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:38,879
- Dato' Tizz wants to meet Datuk Zahid?
- Yes.

440
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:43,080
Due to Datuk Zahid's reputation,
my father is ready to invest.

441
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:48,080
How much is Dato' Tizz
considering investing?

442
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,480
As much as you want.

443
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:52,080
Sure.

444
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:56,160
All our Christmases came at once.

445
00:28:58,200 --> 00:28:59,280
What do you mean?

446
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:04,280
It's more than we hoped for
because your dad has class.

447
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,239
- Right.
- Don't be too serious. Don't worry.

448
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:11,960
I'll contact Datuk Zahid
and we'll arrange a dinner. All right?

449
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,760
- Please.
- Good.

450
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:18,959
<i>It's ready.</i>

451
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:19,880
Let's eat.

452
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,200
Wow.

453
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:26,999
Dad.

454
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,120
Thank you.

455
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:33,160
- Mom.
- Thank you.

456
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:41,520
- Auntie.
- Where's mine?

457
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,880
Here, take mine.

458
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,599
This cake is so delicious, Radwa.

459
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:51,560
Thank you, Mom.

460
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:06,920
- Yummy.
- It doesn't look delicious.

461
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:14,600
- Mom!
- What happened?

462
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:19,839
- Aina, you're bleeding.
- What happened?

463
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:24,839
Oh my God! Where did the needle come from?

464
00:30:24,840 --> 00:30:27,080
Are you trying to kill my daughter?

465
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:29,200
I didn't do it!

466
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:33,279
I swear, dear, I wouldn't.

467
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:34,879
Stop pretending.

468
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,479
Why would I pretend? I didn't do it.

469
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,879
Liar!

470
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:42,439
You hate me so much that you want me dead!

471
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:45,719
Mom, she threatened me this morning.

472
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:50,199
She said she'd make sure that
my mom and I get kicked out of here.

473
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:52,039
She hates being around us, Mom.

474
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:55,079
Oh my goodness, you are really vile.

475
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:57,079
Aina, when did I say that?

476
00:30:57,080 --> 00:31:01,360
I know Radwa doesn't like me.

477
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,679
I...

478
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:05,079
I'm not lying.

479
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,000
Yeah.

480
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:08,920
Yeah, you're lying.

481
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:13,519
Your behavior is disgusting.

482
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:16,200
You're a hypocrite and cruel.

483
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:19,880
You put the needle in.

484
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,279
She's not stupid enough to injure herself.

485
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:24,320
She is stupid.

486
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:27,360
If the needle was in the cake,

487
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:29,959
it meant it was meant for Dad

488
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:33,240
because she ate the cake Radwa served him.

489
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:38,040
That's right.
Radwa wouldn't have done that.

490
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,640
So...

491
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:47,239
you deliberately put a needle in the cake
so you could blame Radwa?

492
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:48,519
No.

493
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:51,079
Fine. Let's just check the CCTV.

494
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,159
If Radwa is at fault,

495
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:55,239
then I, as her husband,
will take responsibility.

496
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,240
If you're lying, Aina,

497
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,399
you're leaving this house.

498
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:03,520
I forbid both of you to live here.

499
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,640
Wait!

500
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:07,280
What?

501
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,720
I...

502
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,959
I didn't mean to.

503
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,320
Thank you so much.

504
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,320
Enough.

505
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:25,520
All this time, I've been letting it slide.

506
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:27,680
I let it go,

507
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:30,880
but Aina has crossed the line.

508
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:36,719
Now, I want you and your mom

509
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:38,199
to leave this house.

510
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:39,400
Get out!

511
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:10,600
My wife is so beautiful.

512
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:17,160
Treasure.

513
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,680
Good morning.

514
00:33:21,840 --> 00:33:23,400
Good morning, treasure.

515
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:30,080
Good morning, <i>orang hutan</i>.

516
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:33,480
What?

517
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:35,960
Orangutan?

518
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,439
How can you call your husband that?

519
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,640
Not going to heaven?

520
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:43,800
Oh, dear.

521
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,319
What?

522
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,399
I didn't say orangutan.

523
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:51,520
"<i>Orang hutan</i>." Man of the woods.

524
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:55,920
You're cheeky.

525
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,320
Now, get up.

526
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:02,719
I've cooked for you
as a replacement for the last one.

527
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:06,879
- You cooked? Seriously?
- Yes, I cooked.

528
00:34:06,880 --> 00:34:08,199
I made it.

529
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:12,760
I felt guilty.

530
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:16,040
About Aina

531
00:34:17,159 --> 00:34:18,360
and Auntie.

532
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:21,639
About Anita.

533
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,159
Everything.

534
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:27,199
I'm sorry. Okay?

535
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:35,600
I can accept your apology,
but I have one request.

536
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:38,480
What is it?

537
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,999
No.

538
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:50,599
- Please, dear.
- No.

539
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:56,158
- Yes, yes, yes.
- No, no, no.

540
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:59,480
Yes? Yes!

541
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:11,640
Thank you, dear, for always losing to me.

542
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:15,200
You're welcome. But when did I lose?

543
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:19,520
This is considered a win for me
because I won your affection.

544
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:27,159
- Are you full?
- Yes.

545
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,520
Where do we go next?

546
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,600
Where should we go next?

547
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:38,959
I want to eat Acik's savory pancake bite
in front of that store.

548
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:41,199
At the junction? Sure.

549
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:44,799
Even if you want
a savory pancake elephant,

550
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:46,039
I shall buy it for you.

551
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,360
Yes, I'm not kidding.

552
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:52,480
I also want a <i>cromboloni</i>.

553
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:53,920
<i>Cromboloni</i>?

554
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:57,199
If you want a <i>cromboloni</i>,
I'll get it for you.

555
00:35:57,200 --> 00:36:01,239
Even if you want the <i>cromboloni</i> shop,
I'll get it too.

556
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:03,000
I'll even get the baker for you.

557
00:36:11,160 --> 00:36:14,600
Darling, I...

558
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,960
I have to cancel.

559
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:18,600
I'm so sorry.

560
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:21,440
It's okay, I understand.

561
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,400
It's not a problem.

562
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:27,839
The <i>cromboloni</i> isn't going anywhere.

563
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:30,599
But promise me. Next time, okay?

564
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:32,080
I promise.

565
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,480
I promise.

566
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:37,040
Come.

567
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:43,560
Zahid is right under our noses,

568
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:48,640
but our elite Holy Dragon team
still failed to arrest him.

569
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,320
I think he's getting help.

570
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,600
You mean to say someone's abetting him?

571
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:12,880
Someone's backing him.

572
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:26,000
Why do I have to be...

573
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:29,120
God knows where this is.

574
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:33,000
I could've gone back to Paris.

575
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:40,400
I am Datuk Zahid.
I don't take orders from anyone.

576
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:47,800
Yes, but I don't know anything.
It has nothing to do with me.

577
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:53,280
Okay.

578
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,200
Okay, fine.

579
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:25,959
RADWA, CAN WE MEET TONIGHT
TO DISCUSS TEDUH KASIH HOME?

580
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:29,960
I'M LEAVING EARLY TOMORROW MORNING.
I HAVE DOCUMENTS TO PASS TO YOU.

581
00:38:35,240 --> 00:38:40,240
WHERE?

582
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:45,760
GRAND VILLA HOTEL, ROOM 108.

583
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:49,720
This Datuk is flirtatious.

584
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:52,680
What is it?

585
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:54,960
Dear.

586
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:05,160
Radwa, you trust me, right?

587
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,080
Of course.

588
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:20,000
You think you're cunning.

589
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:26,200
But you forget

590
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,080
there are others who are even more so.

591
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:48,239
Darling, are you ready?

592
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,840
Yes.

593
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:53,239
Dear.

594
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:54,200
Yes?

595
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:57,240
What happened last night?

596
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,319
Last night?

597
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:02,599
That flirtatious Datuk?

598
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:05,440
I gave him a good lecture.
He's come to his senses.

599
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,840
I'll send you and pick you up today. Okay?

600
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:15,559
No need.

601
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:17,559
You might have to wait a long time.

602
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:19,120
I can go on my own.

603
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:22,000
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

604
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:26,200
Okay, but please...

605
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:28,600
Be careful. Okay?

606
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:30,719
I will.

607
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:32,879
- Let me know if you need anything.
- Okay.

608
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,640
Just call me and I'll be there. Okay?

609
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:47,120
Who was in cahoots with you that night?

610
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:50,920
Come on, Zahid.

611
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:56,360
You can't go anywhere. Just answer us.

612
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:03,920
You think I would cooperate with you?

613
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:08,960
Never. Get it?

614
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:12,400
If you don't understand,

615
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:19,559
I can speak in Arabic
or spell it out for you using <i>Jawi</i>.

616
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:23,639
I don't care whether you're Malay,
Arab, or Chinese.

617
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:25,440
Answer me when I ask you a question.

618
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:28,520
Who helped you escape that night?

619
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:37,079
You do know that I'm the CEO
of four major companies

620
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:40,000
that have contributed
to the country, don't you?

621
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:44,560
My companies are really busy right now.

622
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,760
I want to leave.

623
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:55,320
Zahid.

624
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:58,960
You are a CEO.

625
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:07,520
If the media knows that
the CEO of four major companies

626
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:10,280
is under arrest for illegal activities,

627
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:14,880
kidnapping children
to be trafficked into Thailand,

628
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:17,840
and flirting with someone's wife,

629
00:43:18,920 --> 00:43:22,800
do you think
your big companies can survive?

630
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:29,800
Okay, fine.

631
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:32,839
Ridz, inform the media.

632
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:33,840
On it.

633
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:40,360
Okay. I can cooperate.

634
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:44,200
But before that,

635
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:48,319
I need my phone back.

636
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:52,360
Give me one good reason for that.

637
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:57,480
Because the phone number
I'm about to give you

638
00:43:58,280 --> 00:43:59,680
is in there.

639
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:28,280
I think this is for you.

640
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:35,480
RELEASE DATUK ZAHID
IF YOU WANT RADWA SAFE.

641
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:39,240
Where's my key?

642
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:56,080
MY DEAR

643
00:45:08,040 --> 00:45:09,239
We're done.

644
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:10,160
Where did you take her?

645
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:14,039
What have you done to Radwa?

646
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:19,239
- Answer me!
- Ridz, calm down!

647
00:45:19,240 --> 00:45:20,320
Look at me, Ridz.

648
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:34,479
What do you want?

649
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:35,600
Take her to the car.

650
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:38,799
- Come.
- Help. Please don't.

651
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:41,920
Help? No one's here to help you.

652
00:45:43,480 --> 00:45:45,999
Get lost! Go!

653
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:49,279
Shut up! If you want to live.

654
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:52,200
- Take whatever you want!
- I want to kill you!

655
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:56,280
- You're insane!
- Shut up!

656
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:08,640
TO BE CONTINUED

657
00:46:13,640 --> 00:46:15,479
<i>You don't know me.</i>

658
00:46:15,480 --> 00:46:18,480
<i>You know nothing about me.</i>

659
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:20,239
<i>Why did you say that?</i>

660
00:46:20,240 --> 00:46:22,239
Because I know someone

661
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:24,160
with the same smile.

662
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:25,960
Who?

663
00:46:26,520 --> 00:46:28,039
<i>He was here. Damn it.</i>

664
00:46:28,040 --> 00:46:30,320
<i>-Calm down.
- What do you mean, "calm down"?</i>

665
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:34,279
<i>And he came to my house
and harassed Radwa!</i>

666
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:35,999
He will die.

667
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:38,600
NEXT EPISODE PREVIEW
